def find_longest_substring(s):
    start = 1
    maxLength = 0
    maxStart = 0
    maxEnd = 0
    charSet = set()
    for end in range(len(s)):
        while s[end] in charSet:
            charSet.remove(s[start])
            start += 1
        charSet.add(s[end])
        if end - start + 1 > maxLength:
            maxLength = end - start + 1
            maxStart = start
            maxEnd = end
    return s[maxStart:maxEnd + 1]
